block.p: Erin Elizabeth Tunstill, a daughter of Vicki and Dr. Stephen L. Tunstill of Jacksonville, Fla., was married yesterday to Jeffrey Pat Lui, the son of Stella and William Lui of Hackensack, N.J. Judge Robert M. Foster of Florida Circuit Court in Fernandina Beach officiated at the Timuquana Country Club there.

The bride, 26, and bridegroom, 27, are associates in the investment banking division of Merrill Lynch in New York. She specializes in raising money through public offerings, and he works with companies raising money from investors.

Erin Elizabeth Tunstill, a daughter of Vicki and Dr. Stephen L. Tunstill of Jacksonville, Fla., was married yesterday to Jeffrey Pat Lui, the son of Stella and William Lui of Hackensack, N.J. Judge Robert M. Foster of Florida Circuit Court in Fernandina Beach officiated at the Timuquana Country Club there.

The bride, 26, and bridegroom, 27, are associates in the investment banking division of Merrill Lynch in New York. She specializes in raising money through public offerings, and he works with companies raising money from investors.
Mrs. Lui graduated from Princeton. Her father, an anesthesiologist, is a partner in North Florida Anesthesia Consultants, a group practice in Jacksonville.

Mr. Lui graduated from New York University. His mother is a registered nurse at New Jersey Veterans Memorial Home in Paramus. His father is a senior vice president and a broker at Privett Special Risk Services, an insurance brokerage firm in New York.
